added.title: Terra-ized

added.title: Secret Book Club

added.description: Onion must stop Apple from falling prey to his obsession, but a certain phone game is proving to be quite an obstacle.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish

added.title: Apple's Formula
added.description: Apple needs to find a formula for comedy that will land him a movie role.

added.title: River of Gold
added.description: Apple and Onion find a mysterious book but they better read it fast before it disappears forever.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Log Date 7 15 2

added.title: Barn Mates

added.title: Elements Part 1: Skyhooks

added.title: Elements Part 2: Bespoken For
added.description: Ice King weaves a tale filled with drama, romance, and men's fashion.

added.title: Elements Part 3: Winter Light
added.description: Finn, Jake, and Ice King travel to the new Ice Kingdom to confront the person responsible for turning everything topsy-turvy.

added.title: Elements Part 4: Cloudy
added.description: Before they can restore Ooo, Finn and Jake will have to escape exile in an endless sky.

added.title: Elements Part 5: Slime Central
added.description: Finn and Jake infiltrate the new Slime Kingdom and are drawn into a heated skate battle.

added.title: This is My Jam
added.description: Rigby gets a terrible, terrible song stuck in his head and will go to any lengths to get it out.

added.title: Temp Check

added.title: Jinx
added.description: Rigby must figure out how to unjinx himself without talking.

added.title: See You There
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby find out that everyone has been invited by Muscle Man to High Five Ghost's birthday party except them. They decide to go anyway.

added.title: Do Me a Solid
added.description: Mordecai owes Rigby big time when he agrees to go on a double date with him.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

added.title: Seed No Evil/City of Clipsville
added.description: Seed No Evil: When a prehistoric caveman thaws out in Townsville, the girls must stop him from stealing the Mayor's seeds./City of Clipsville: The girls reminisce on their adventures in these new, never-before-seen clips!

added.title: Pee Pee G's/Boy Toys
added.description: The Pee Pee G's: When the girls wake up to discover their bed is wet, none of them want to admit that they are the guilty party./Boy Toys: The girls allow Princess to become a Powerpuff Girl when they realize they need help trying to defeat the Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: The Boys Are Back in Town
added.description: Him brings the Rowdyruff Boys back, protecting them from the girls' feminine wiles.

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Find Your Bliss
added.description: When Bubbles blames a string of accidents on her imaginary friend Bliss, her sisters begin to think she's lost her mind.

added.title: Bliss Reminisce
added.description: The Girls learn Bliss' backstory from the Professor, Mojo Jojo, and Bliss herself.

added.title: Blisster Sister
added.description: The Girls hang out with their new big sister Bliss, who gets a taste of fighting bad guys as part of the Powerpuff Girls.

added.title: Breaking Bliss
added.description: When Bliss struggles to control her powers an evil force arises to take advantage.

added.title: Chair
added.description: Unikitty finds an old, beatup recliner on the curb, but sees its inner beauty and brings it home to introduce to the gang! In a series of absurd and fun vignettes, we discover how a dirty, inanimate chair comes into each of their lives and changes them for the better. We soon learn that dear, sweet Chair was too good for this world.

added.title: Kickflip McPuppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn wants to impress his skater friends with his sweet skills, except he has none. Hoping to boost his confidence, Unikitty and the gang put on Dr. Fox's invisibility suits to secretly help him pull off impossible moves! But they do their job too well and "pro skater" Puppycorn is invited to showcase his skills in a dangerous stunt competition. How far will the gang go to help the pup live out his rad pipe dreams?

added.title: Super Amazing Raft Adventure
added.description: Unikitty and Hawkodile are "lost at sea", stranded on a raft together. Hawkodile sees this as an opportunity to show Unikitty that he's prepared for anything with his expertly-honed survival skills, but to his shock, all of his plans keep falling apart, while Unikitty's silly "it'll all work out, let's have fun" approach is somehow working great! Will Hawkodile manage to let go of his overpreparedness to save them both, or will Unikitty whimsical fun be their doom?

added.title: Tasty Heist
added.description: Richard's prepared one of the tastiest desserts ever, but he's locked it up tight until the friends have their boring dinner. This will not stand. Unikitty organizes a heist, assembling the friends as a crack team to get in, get out, and eat that tasty snack without Richard knowing. But this heist has hiccups. Can the friends take the cake?

added.title: Brawl Bot
added.description: Dr. Fox is proud to unveil her new ultimate combat machine and take it into an underground scientist fighting ring. But Hawkodile's jealous of Dr. Fox's fighting bot that's supposedly a better puncher than him and declares he can beat anything it can. To prove his point, he dresses up in spare robot parts and enters himself secretly in the bot battle. With Unikitty as his fighting coach, can Hawkodile survive the tourney, prove he's tougher than a machine, and avoid the scrap yard?

added.title: Bucky and the Howl
added.description: After Clarence learns Sumo's in the school musical, he joins up and enthusiastically promotes the show. On opening night with a packed house, stage fright takes hold of Sumo and he runs off leaving Clarence to go on alone.

added.title: Worm Bin
added.description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Birthday
added.description: Jeff and Sumo expect no one to show at Clarence's birthday party, just like last year. When dozens of kids arrive, the boys struggle to get face time with Clarence, the popular party host.

added.title: Tree of Life
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo make it their mission to climb a really tall tree before it's set to be chopped down. As they scale higher and higher their reality begins to slip away.

added.title: The Little Mer-Tiger
added.description: The origin of Tiger is told as a flashback.  As the legend goes, Tiger used to be a mermaid.  One day the evil ruler of the sea, Bubble Grandpa, demanded a hamburger and picked Tiger to retrieve it.  He used his magic sea powers to give Tiger legs and send her ashore.  But Tiger grew to love the land, and with the help of her new friend, Uncle Grandpa, defeated the evil sea ruler and got to keep her legs.

added.title: Ballroom
added.description: MG fixes up the ballroom and warns UG and PS not to step a foot in there until he gets a chance to use it.  But UG mistakenly tosses a ball into the room.  Now PS and UG have to retrieve the ball without touching one foot to the ground.

added.title: Back to the Library
added.description: Uncle Grandpa uses time travel to convince his past self to return a library book on time.

added.title: Uncle Easter
added.description: The Easter Bunny, unable to fulfill his egg-delivering duties, has Uncle Grandpa fill in for him.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.
